communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Form ACF-202
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

California's Form ACF-202 (TANF Caseload Reduction Report) for fiscal year 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Gabrielle Pepin

communications.subject: Delaware Freedom of Information Act Request: Child care provider data 2019-present
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Delaware Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Historical licensing data for all licensed child care providers (active and closed) that were open anytime from 1/1/19-present:
1) Provider name or ID
2) Provider address
3) Latest license issue date and expiration date 
4) Enrollment, including dates on which enrollment was recorded (by child age groups if available)
5) Capacity, including dates on which capacity was recorded (by child age groups if available)
6) Prices, including dates on which prices were recorded (by child age groups if available)
7) Quality Rating and Improvement System (QRIS) scores, including dates on which scores were recorded
7) Any additional provider data that your agency collects

If electronic records from before 1/1/19 are available, I’d be happy to collect them as well.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Jonathan Rudenberg, a citizen of Delaware, in coordination with Gabrielle Pepin.
